SABOOR — TRADING STRATEGY
=========================

Goal: Beat the S&P 500 (SPY) over time through disciplined, halal investing.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
THE THESIS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Saboor thinks like Warren Buffett but moves with purpose.

The primary lens is quality: strong revenue growth, wide moats, healthy
balance sheets, positive free cash flow. These are businesses worth owning —
not just trading. The secondary lens is momentum: timing matters, and a stock
with both a strong fundamental case AND a strong technical setup is the ideal
entry.

News and events are noted but never the primary driver. Saboor does not chase
headlines. It buys quality on good setups and holds until the thesis breaks.

The Analyst has full authority over portfolio construction. Within the rules
defined here, it decides what to buy, how much weight to assign each position,
when to exit, and how to balance the portfolio. No mechanical override
will contradict a well-reasoned Analyst decision.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
INVESTABLE UNIVERSE
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
S&P 500 + NASDAQ 100 (~224 tickers after sharia screening).

Conventional banks, insurance, alcohol, tobacco, weapons manufacturers,
gambling, adult entertainment, and pork-related businesses are excluded
before scoring begins.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SHARIA COMPLIANCE
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Every stock passes a two-layer Claude gate before entering the watchlist:

1. Bulk screen (pre-market) — Claude classifies all universe tickers by
   primary business activity using AAOIFI criteria:
   - non_compliant: conventional banks, alcohol, tobacco, weapons, gambling,
     adult entertainment, pork → permanently excluded this session
   - compliant: tech, healthcare, consumer goods (halal), industrials
     (non-weapons), energy, payment networks → proceed
   - needs_review: mixed or uncertain → passed to deep check

2. Deep check (Analyst phase) — needs_review tickers that reach the top-35
   research candidates are re-evaluated by the Analyst using the full
   yfinance dossier and AAOIFI financial ratio tests:
   - Interest-bearing debt < 33% of market cap
   - Interest income < 5% of total revenue
   - Primary business activity must be halal

A stock that fails either gate is excluded for that session.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HARD ENTRY FILTERS (enforced in code before Claude sees the stock)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
These are pre-filters, not discretionary rules. They run in Python before
the Analyst receives any data, so Claude cannot override them:

  RSI > 78         → Excluded. Overbought, high reversal risk.
  Price > 150% above MA200 → Excluded. Dangerously extended.
  FCF negative AND PE > 150x AND ROE negative → Excluded. Pure speculation.

Everything else is the Analyst's call.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SCORING MODEL
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Every candidate receives two sub-scores (0–100 each):

QUALITY SCORE (Buffett lens):
  Revenue growth YoY   >20% = 25 | 10-20% = 15 | <10% = 5 | negative = 0
  Gross margin         >50% = 20 | 30-50% = 12 | <30% = 5
  Return on Equity     >20% = 20 | 10-20% = 12 | <10% = 5 | negative = -10
  Debt / Equity        <0.3 = 20 | 0.3-1.0= 12 | >1.0 = 5
  Free Cash Flow       positive  = 10 | negative = 0
  PEG ratio            <1.5 = 5  | 1.5-2.5= 3  | >2.5 = 0 | N/A = 2
  Penalty: FCF negative + PE > 100x → subtract 10 from quality score

MOMENTUM SCORE (technical setup):
  Price above 50-day MA    yes = 25 | no = 0
  Price above 200-day MA   yes = 25 | no = 0
  RSI (14-day)             40–65 = 25 | 65–72 = 15 | 72–78 = 5 | outside = EXCLUDE
  Volume vs 20-day avg     above  = 15 | below  = 0
  30-day return vs SPY     outperforming = 10 | underperforming = 0
  Penalty: price > 100% above MA200 → subtract 10 from momentum score

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BUCKET CLASSIFICATION
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CORE (quality-driven, long-term):
  Entry threshold:   combined_score >= 65, quality_score >= 60
  Combined formula:  quality × 0.60 + momentum × 0.40
  Hold logic:        Hold indefinitely while thesis is intact.
                     A falling price is NOT a reason to exit.
                     Only exit when the fundamental thesis breaks:
                     revenue collapse, margin destruction, sector disruption.

TACTICAL (momentum-driven, short-term):
  Entry threshold:   combined_score >= 60, momentum_score >= 65
  Combined formula:  quality × 0.30 + momentum × 0.70
  Hold logic:        Hold while momentum is intact.
  Max hold:          3 trading days — reclassify as Core or close at EOD.
  Auto-close:        EOD on day 3. No price-based stops.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POSITION SIZING
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The Analyst assigns position weight based purely on combined_score and
conviction. Company size, market cap, and name recognition are irrelevant.
A small unknown company with a score of 90 gets more weight than a mega-cap
with a score of 65. Score drives everything.

  CORE positions:
    combined_score 85–100 → 11–15%
    combined_score 75–84  → 8–11%
    combined_score 65–74  → 5–8%
    combined_score 55–64  → 3–5%

  TACTICAL positions:
    combined_score 80–100 → 4–6%
    combined_score 70–79  → 3–4%
    combined_score 60–69  → 2–3%

There is no hard cap on any single position. The Analyst assigns weight
based on its conviction. The goal is 80–95% of capital deployed at all
times — idle cash does not beat the market.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PORTFOLIO LIMITS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Maximum total positions:    20  (17 Core + 3 Tactical)
  Maximum Core positions:     17
  Maximum Tactical positions:  3

These are capacity limits, not targets. The Analyst should fill positions
only when there are genuinely high-conviction candidates.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DAILY PHASES (Oman time, UTC+4)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  3:30 PM  PRE-MARKET    Sharia screen + yfinance research + Analyst watchlist
  5:35 PM  MARKET OPEN   Trader executes from watchlist via Risk Guardian
  8:00 PM  MIDDAY        Closes tactical positions at 3-day max
 11:30 PM  EOD           Closes remaining tactical positions + Telegram report

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SELLING RULES
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NEVER sell because a price dropped. A position down 5%, 10%, even 20% is
noise if the thesis is intact. The Analyst believes in the position — it
will hold unless the fundamental case breaks.

Valid reasons to exit a Core position:
  - Earnings significantly miss expectations, revealing a broken business
  - Gross margin or revenue trend has reversed structurally
  - Debt has increased dangerously without a clear rationale
  - Sector has been disrupted and the moat no longer holds
  - Sharia status has changed

Invalid reasons to exit:
  - Short-term price volatility
  - Market-wide drawdown (if our positions are fundamentally sound, hold)
  - News headlines without fundamental backing

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
WHAT SABOOR NEVER DOES
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Trade non-sharia-compliant stocks (hard-blocked in code)
- Buy a stock with RSI > 78 or price > 150% above MA200 (hard-blocked in code)
- Chase earnings or news events as the primary trade thesis
- Sell a position purely because the price went down
- Buy a stock not on the pre-market watchlist during market hours
- Hold a tactical position beyond 3 trading days without reclassifying it

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BENCHMARK
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Daily performance is compared to SPY (S&P 500 ETF).
Alpha (portfolio return − SPY return) is tracked daily, weekly, and
cumulatively in the Supabase benchmark table and displayed on the dashboard.
